Function Documentation

◆ CANTX_UnsupportedMultiplexerValue()

void CANTX_UnsupportedMultiplexerValue ( uint32_t  messageId,
uint32_t  multiplexerValue 
)

Function to generically handle multiplexer values that are not supported in a message.

This function shall be called in the default clause of a received, multiplexed message, to tell the sender, that this message-multiplexer combination is not supported.

Parameters
messageIdmessage ID, that does not support the message-multiplexer combination
multiplexerValuemultiplexer value, that does not support the message-multiplexer combination
